Title : Richard Mawarden
Text : {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2016}}
{{Use British English|date=November 2016}}
'''Richard Mawarden''' (died c. 1418), of [[Marden, Herefordshire|Marden]], [[Herefordshire]], [[Sodbury]], [[Gloucestershire]] and [[Stratford-sub-Castle]], [[Wiltshire]], was an English politician.

He was a [[Member of Parliament|Member]] (MP) of the [[Parliament of England]] for [[Herefordshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Herefordshire]] in April 1384, for [[Wiltshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Wiltshire]] in January 1404 and for [[Gloucestershire (UK Parliament constituency)|Gloucestershire]] in October 1404.<ref>http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1386-1421/member/mawarden-richard-1418</ref>

